---
import Base from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<Base title="Open Source"><Fragment slot="header"><Header /></Fragment>

  <section class="pt-28 pb-16" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#f8faff 0%,#ffffff 50%,#f5f3ff 100%)">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8"><div class="max-w-2xl"><p class="sl">Community</p><h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-gray-900 leading-tight mb-4">Open source</h1><p class="text-lg text-gray-500 max-w-xl">Every platform, pipeline, and standard we build is released openly. The infrastructure layer of genomics should be a shared resource.</p></div></div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 border-t border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose space-y-8">
        <div><h2>Our Commitment</h2><p>All software tools, analysis pipelines, and statistical methods developed at Protomon Labs are released under open-source licences. We maintain active repositories on GitHub.</p></div>
        <div><h2>Licensing</h2><p><strong>MIT License:</strong> Used for most software tools, utility libraries, and analysis scripts.</p><p><strong>GNU GPL v3:</strong> Used for core statistical method implementations and pipeline frameworks.</p></div>
        <div><h2>Repositories</h2><p>variant-impact-prediction · global-rare-variants · eqtl-admixed · variant-annotation-benchmark</p></div>
        <div><h2>Contributing</h2><p>We welcome contributions. See CONTRIBUTING.md in each repository.</p></div>
        <div><h2>Contact</h2><p>hello@protomonlabs.org</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

<Fragment slot="footer"><Footer /></Fragment></Base>